Death of Virgin. Right part certainly connected with Schongauer engraving B. [Bartsch] 33. Position of Bed and arrangement of curtain with one part tied up: the candle being put into her hands from left, altitude of St.John (Schongauer) and St.Peter (Bruegel) in placing the candle rather similar. Also the bed cover raised because of the Virgins legs; Ad [Addendum] Death of Virgin: see R.
